<TITLE> MP's sons charged with assault, minister vows action </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Oct 8 (bdnews24.com)--Sons of a ruling party MP have been charged with assaulting journalists in Kumira coastal area in Sitakunda. The perpetrators of the assault would be brought to book, the state minister for home, Shamsul Haque Tuku, later said. Photo journalist of the Daily Prothom Alo Rashid Mahmud filed the case with Sitakunda police station early on Thursday. Mahmud accused 20 people including S M Al-Mamun and S M Al-Noman--sons of MP A B M Abul Kashem Master and nephew Mahmudul Islam Manna-- of beating up him and his associates, threatening them with death and damaging their cameras. Abdul Bayes, assistant sub-inspestor of Sitakunda Police Station, confirmed the the filing of the case. He told bdnews24.com that nobody was arrested until noon. On Wednesday, Al-Mamun and Al-Noman, aided by a group of miscreants, allegedly stormed four shipyards and hung a signboard of Unique Enterprise, a firm owned by Mamun, one of the accused. Mahmud, staff reporter Pronab Paul and Sitakunda Press Club president Forkan Abu came under attack as they rushed to the spot to cover the news. Tuku said: "Legal action is being taken against those responsible for this unwanted incident. "Nobody will be spared," the minister told reporters at the Secretariat. Referring to the land grabbing, he said, "The evil culture has not developed overnight. But we want to get rid of this legacy." bdne
